<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006, &ldquo;&Agrave; propos du nom propre
dans l&rsquo;Antiquit&eacute;: quelques points qui ont fait
d&eacute;bat&rdquo;, <em>Corpus</em>, 50, pp. 229&ndash;237.</li>

<li>Black, Deborah, 2011, &ldquo;Avicenna&rsquo;s &lsquo;Vague
Individuals&rsquo; and its Impact on Medieval Latin Philosophy&rdquo;,
in Robert Wisnovsky, Faith Wallis, Jamie Fumo, and Carlos Fraenkel
(eds.), <em>Vehicles of Transmission, Translation, and Transformation
in Medieval Textual Culture</em>, Turnhout: Brepols, pp.
259&ndash;292</li>

<li>Bos, Egbert, 1999, &ldquo;Thuo of Viborg and Marsilius of
Inghen&rdquo;, in Sten Ebbesen and Russell L. Friedman (eds.),
<em>Medieval Analyses on Language and Cognition</em>, Copenhagen, pp.
323&ndash;340.</li>

<li>Brumberg-Chaumont, Julie, 2005, &ldquo;La nomination du singulier
dans les <em>Quaestiones super Metaphysicam</em>, de Geoffroy
d&rsquo;Aspall,&rdquo; <em>Archives d&rsquo;histoire doctrinale et
litt&eacute;raire du moyen &acirc;ge</em>, 72: 47&ndash;103.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2007, &ldquo;S&eacute;mantiques du nom
propre: sources anciennes et discussions m&eacute;di&eacute;vales
&agrave; l&rsquo;&eacute;poque d&rsquo;Ab&eacute;lard,&rdquo;
<em>Histoire &Eacute;pist&eacute;mologie Langage</em>, 29:
137&ndash;166.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2007 [2011], &ldquo;Les sens de
&lsquo;Substance&rsquo; chez Apollonius Dyscole&rdquo;, <em>Lettras
Classicas</em>, 11: 11&ndash;50.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, &ldquo;La signification de la
substance chez Priscien et Pierre H&eacute;lie&rdquo;, in Louis Holtz,
Marc Baratin, Bernard Colombat (eds.), <em>Priscien: Transmission et
refondation de la grammaire de l&rsquo;Antiquit&eacute; aux
Modernes</em>, Turnhout: Brepols, pp. 503&ndash;519.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, &ldquo;Grammaire et logique du nom
dans les <em>Gloses</em> sur Priscien de Guillaume de Conches&rdquo;,
in Barbara Obrist and Irene Caiazzo (eds.), <em>Guillaume de Conches:
philosophie et science au XIIe si&egrave;cle</em>, Firenze: Sismel,
pp. 377&ndash;465.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013a. &ldquo;The Logical and Grammatical
Contribution to the Reflection on Individuality in Late
Antiquity&rdquo;, in Johannes Zachhuber and Alexis Torrens eds.),
<em>Individuality in Late Antiquity</em>, Burlington: Ashgate, pp.
63&ndash;90.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013b. &ldquo;The Role of Discrete Terms in
the Theory of the Properties of Terms,&rdquo; <em>Vivarium</em>, 51:
169&ndash;204.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2016, &ldquo;Jean Buridan et le
probl&egrave;me des termes singuliers substantiels&rdquo;,
<em>Documenti e Studi sulla tradizione filosofica medievale</em>,
XXVII: 411&ndash;451.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, forthcoming-a, &ldquo;Sophismatically
Thinking about consequences from universal to singular propositions. A
case study from the <em>sophisma</em> OMNIS HOMO DE NECESSITATE EST
ANIMA&rdquo;, in Alain de Libera, Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Goubier, and
Laurent Cesalli (eds.), <em>Sophismata: histoire d&rsquo;une pratique
philosophique</em>, Schwabe.
 [<a href="https://hal.science/hal-04337300v1/document" target="other">Preprint of Brumberg-Chaumont forthcoming-a available online</a></li>
 
<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, forthcoming-b, &ldquo;Logiques du nom
propres, de l&rsquo;Antiquit&eacute; au Moyen &Acirc;ge&rdquo;, in
Bernard Bosredon, Georges Kleiber, and Irene Tamba (eds.),
<em>Nomination, r&eacute;f&eacute;rence et signification &agrave;
l&rsquo;&eacute;preuve du nom propre</em>, London: Iste Editions.</li>

<li>Brunschwig, Jacques, 1984, &ldquo;Remarques sur la th&eacute;orie
Sto&iuml;cienne du nom propre,&rdquo; <em>Histoire
&Eacute;pist&eacute;mologie Langage</em>, 6: 3&ndash;19.</li>

<li>Chiaradonna, Riccardo, 2000. &ldquo;La teoria dell&rsquo;individuo
in Porfirio e l&rsquo;IDI&Ocirc;S POION stoico&rdquo;,
<em>Elenchos</em>, XXI(2): 303&ndash;331.</li>

<li>Dutilh-Novaes, Catarina, 2012. &ldquo;A Medieval Solution to the
Problem of Empty Names,&rdquo; in Catarina Dutilh-Novaes and Ole
Thomassen Hjortland (eds.), <em>Insolubles and Consequences, Essays in
Honour of Stephen Read</em>, London: College Publications, pp.
73&ndash;92.</li>

<li>Ebbesen, Sten, 1987, &ldquo;Talking about what is no more. Texts
by Peter of Cornwall(?), Richard of Clive, Simon of Faversham, and
Radulphus Brito. A Supplement to CIMAGL 3,&rdquo; <em>Cahiers de
l&rsquo;institut du moyen-&acirc;ge grec et latin</em>, 55:
135&ndash;68.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2000, &ldquo;Words and Signification in the
13th Century Questions on Aristotle&rsquo;s
<em>Metaphysics&rdquo;</em>, <em>Cahiers de l&rsquo;Institut du Moyen
Age Grec et Latin</em>, 70: 74&ndash;114.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013,&ldquo;Early supposition theory
II&rdquo;, <em>Vivarium</em>, 51(1&ndash;4): 60&ndash;78.</li>

<li>Ebbesen, Sten, and Pinborg, Jan, 1984, &ldquo;Thirteenth century
notes on William of Sherwood&rsquo;s Treatise on Properties of Terms,
an edition of <em>Anonymi Dubitationes et Notabilia circa Guilelmi de
Shyreswode Introductionum Logicalium Tractatum V</em> from Ms.
Worcester Cath. Q. 13,&rdquo; <em>Cahiers de l&rsquo;Institut du Moyen
&Acirc;ge Grec et Latin</em>, 47: 104&ndash;141</li>

<li>Ebbesen, Sten, Goubier, Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric, 2010, <em>A
Catalogue of Thirteenth Century Sophismata</em>, vols. I et II, Paris:
Vrin.</li>

<li>Fredborg, Karin Margareta, 1973, &ldquo;The Dependence of Petrus
Helias&rsquo; <em>Summa super Priscianum</em> on William of
Conches&rsquo; <em>Glose super Priscianum</em>,&rdquo; <em>Cahiers de
l&rsquo;Institut du Moyen &Acirc;ge Grec et Latin</em>, 11:
1&ndash;57.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1988, &ldquo;Speculative Grammar,&rdquo; in
Peter Dronke (ed.), <em>A History of Twelfth-Century Western
Philosophy</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, pp.
177&ndash;195.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, &ldquo;William of Conches and His
Grammar,&rdquo; in Barabra Obrist and Irene Caiazzo (eds.),
<em>Guillaume de Conches: philosophie et science au XIIe
si&egrave;cle</em>, Firenze: Sismel, pp. 329&ndash;376.</li>

<li>Gazziero, Leone, Libera, Alain de, 2008, &ldquo;Le
<em>sophisma</em> &lsquo;<em>Omnis homo de necessitate est
animal</em>&rsquo; du codex Parisinus 16135, f. 99rb-103vb&rdquo;,
<em>Archives d&rsquo;Histoire Doctrinale et Litt&eacute;raire du Moyen
&Acirc;ge</em>, 75: 323&ndash;368.</li>

<li>Gelber, Hester G., 2004, <em>It Could Have Been Otherwise,
Contingency and Necessity in the Dominican Theology at Oxford,
1300&ndash;1350</em>, Leiden/Boston: Brill.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1974, <em>Logic and the Trinity. A Clash of
Value in Scholastic Thought, 1300&ndash;1300</em>, Ph.D. Thesis,
Madison, University of Wisconsin.</li>

<li>Goubier, Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric, Rosier-Catach, Ir&egrave;ne,
2019, &ldquo;The <em>Trivium</em> in the 12th century&rdquo;, in
C&eacute;dric Giraud (ed.), <em>Les &eacute;coles du XIIe
si&egrave;cle</em>, Leiden: Brill, pp. 141&ndash;179.</li>

<li>Gourinat, Jean-Baptiste, 2000, <em>La dialectique des
Sto&iuml;ciens</em>, Paris: Vrin.</li>

<li>Gracia, Jorge J. E., 1984, <em>Introduction to the Problem of
Individuation in the Early Middle Ages</em>, Washington, D. C.: The
Catholic University of America Press.</li>

<li>Grondeux, Anne, and Rosier-Catach, Ir&egrave;ne, 2017,
<em>Priscien lu par Guillaume de Champeaux et son &eacute;cole</em>:
<em>Les Notae Dunelmenses</em> (Durham, D. C. L., C.IV.29), Turnhout:
Brepols.</li>

<li>Holtz, Louis, <em>et al</em>., 2009, <em>Priscien: Transmission et
refondation de la grammaire de l&rsquo;Antiquit&eacute; aux
Modernes</em>, Turnhout: Brepols.</li>

<li>Kalligas, Peter, 2002, &ldquo;Basil of Caesarea on Proper
Names&rdquo;, in Katerina Ierodiakonou (ed.), <em>Byzantine Philosophy
and its Ancient Sources</em>, Oxford: Clrendon Press, pp.
31&ndash;48</li>

<li>King, Peter, 1994, &ldquo;Buridan on Individuation&rdquo;, in
Jorge E. Gracia (ed.), <em>Individuation in Scholasticism</em>,
Albany: State University of New York Press, pp. 397&ndash;430.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; 2001, &ldquo;John Buridan&rsquo;s Solution
to the Problem of Universals,&rdquo; in J. M. M. H. Thijssen and Jack
Zupko (eds.), <em>The Metaphysics and Natural Philosophy of John
Buridan</em>, Leiden-Boston-K&ouml;ln: Brill, pp. 1&ndash;28.</li>

<li>Klima, Gyula, 2009, <em>John Buridan</em>, Great Medieval
Thinkers, Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, &ldquo;The Medieval Problem of
Singulars&rdquo;, in Gyula Klima and Alexander Hall (eds.), <em>The
