247&ndash;95.</li>

<li>Marmo, Costantino, 1994, <em>La semiotica dei modisti</em>, Roma:
Istituto Storico Italiano per il Medioevo.</li>

<li>Miller, Richard H., 1985, &ldquo;Buridan on Singular
Concepts&rdquo;, <em>Franciscan Studies</em>, 45: 57&ndash;72.</li>

<li>Mora-M&aacute;rquez, Ana Maria, 2019,&ldquo;Singular Intellection
in Medieval Commentaries on Arstotle&rsquo;s <em>De anima</em>&rdquo;,
<em>Vivarium</em>, 57: 293&ndash;316.</li>

<li>Perreiah, Alan R., 1972, &ldquo;Buridan and the Definite
Description,&rdquo; <em>Journal of the History of Philosophy</em>, 10:
153&ndash;60.</li>

<li>Panaccio, Claude, 2006 [2017], &ldquo;Subordination et
singularit&eacute;, la th&eacute;orie ockhamiste des propositions
singuli&egrave;res&rdquo;, <em>Cahiers
d&rsquo;&Eacute;pist&eacute;mologie</em>, Universit&eacute; du
Qu&eacute;bec &agrave; Montr&eacute;al, Cahier num. 269; reprinted in
M. P&eacute;charman, Ph. De Roulhan (eds.), <em>Le Philosophe et le
langage</em>, Paris: Vrin, 2017, pp. 75&ndash;98.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1980, &ldquo;Occam et les
D&eacute;monstratifs&rdquo;, in E. F. Konrad Koerner et al. (eds.),
<em>Studies in the History of Linguistics Dedicated to Geoffrey L.
